{{Evolution-stub}}

{{unreferenced|date=September 2016}}
The '''Eastern Mediterranean conifer-sclerophyllous-broadleaf forests''' [[terrestrial ecoregion|ecoregion]], in the [[Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub]] [[biome]], is of the eastern [[Mediterranean Basin]].

==Setting==
The ecoregion covers an area of {{convert|143,800|km2|sqmi|sp=us}}, and covers portions of [[Israel]], the [[Palestinian territories]], [[Jordan]], [[Lebanon]], [[Syria]], and [[Turkey]].

==Flora==
Major plant communities in the ecoregion include broadleaf [[sclerophyll]]ous shrublands ([[maquis shrublands|maquis]]), [[pine]] forests (chiefly of [[Aleppo Pine]] ''(Pinus halepensis)'' and [[Turkish Pine]] ''(Pinus brutia'')), and dry oak (''Quercus'' spp.) woodlands and steppes.

