'''RunWise''' is an [[energy recovery]] project within the [[Parker Hannifin Corporation]].  The plans of this project are: being part of the [[powertrain]] on [[truck]]s performing multiple stop and go cycles, the Runwise system will store energy from vehicle [[Brake|braking]] into [[Accumulator (energy)|accumulator]]s, releasing the power again for acceleration.

[[Autocar Company|Autocar]], maker of severe service trucks, is partnering with Parker Hannifin to release a refuse truck utilizing the RunWise system.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ccjdigital.com/parker-designs-runwise-hybrid-for-refuse-vehicles-2/ |title=Parker designs RunWise hybrid for refuse vehicles |publisher=CCJ |date={{Date|2009-06-15}} }}</ref>

