{{Christian-theology-stub}}

'''Wuluwait''' is a god from northern [[Arnhem Land]] (in northern Australia) and is known to work with [[Bunbulama]] as a rainmaker. He is also recorded by [[Charles Mountford]] and [[Ainslie Roberts]] as a boatman who ferries the souls of the dead to Purelko, the aboriginal afterlife.

